How the f**k can he be offside when:
1. The ball is going backwards
2. Neto is running back onside so he can receive the ball.
3. It doesn't give Wolves any advantage, having Neto's heel offside by a fraction when he is clearly f***ing running away from the goal.
Seriously VAR needs to be shut down or the offside rule needs to be changed because it is ruining football. Not just for Wolves but they have now had 11 goals now disallowed because of VAR.

snippet.textDisplay:
Only the most robotic, emotionless, soulless ,armchair-sitting nerd can believe these marginal technicalities are good for the game...
Completely against the spirit of a Sport that is supposed to be in The Entertainment Industry. It just makes mockery of attackers no longer getting " The Benefit Of The Doubt".
Thankfully ( for me ) I attended over 2,000 games and watched thousands of others since 1962 without VAR....

snippet.textDisplay: At this point we just have to sit tight and wait for next season with renewed offside laws because it's utter anti football bullshit. People don't pay their hard earned money to watch goals ruled out for heels and armpits being "offside". Change it so any part of the attacker is onside, then it's onside. That could mean a heel, if it's still level with the defender, then it's onside. Nobody is going to complain about that. 6 months to go.
